#Thigs to do before starting any project:-

1*create folder.
2*open terminal and move on that folder by(cd ..).
3*create virtual environment on that folder:-
 In some systems, it is recommended to have installed python-dev to run virtualenv successfully. Itâ€™s also important to upgrade pip to the latest version before the installation of virtualenv.
	.pip install virtualenv
	.virtualenv env -p python3. or virtualenv -p python3 venv.
	.source env/bin/activate

4*Install the required packages:
	.pip install django.

5*Create a new django project and move on that folder(cd ..):
	.django-admin startproject projectname.

6*Create a new app:-
	.python manage.yp startapp appname

7*pip install -r requirements.txt (if requirment file is present in project)


+========================================================================================================

How to install virtualenv:
Install pip first

sudo apt-get install python3-pip

Then install virtualenv using pip3

sudo pip3 install virtualenv 

Now create a virtual environment

virtualenv venv 

    you can use any name insted of venv

You can also use a Python interpreter of your choice

virtualenv -p /usr/bin/python2.7 venv

Active your virtual environment:

source venv/bin/activate
	
